SIMPLE: involuntary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Involuntary
<hw>In*vol"un*ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>involuntarius</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Voluntary</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not having will or the power of choice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not under the influence or control of the will; not
voluntary; <as>as, the <ex>involuntary</ex> movements of the body;
<ex>involuntary</ex> muscle fibers.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not proceeding from choice; done unwillingly;
reluctant; compulsory; <as>as, <ex>involuntary</ex>
submission</as>.</def></p>

<p><ent>Involuted</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Involute</ent>⟦br⟧
